  <!-- Test 1: Basic MathML equation (E=mc²) -->
  <entry>
    <title>Einstein's Mass-Energy Equivalence</title>
    <link href="https://example.com/mathml1"/>
    <id>https://example.com/mathml1</id>
    <updated>2006-04-15T12:00:00Z</updated>
    <content type="xhtml">
      <div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
        <p>Einstein's most famous equation:</p>
        <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block">
          <mi>E</mi>
          <mo>=</mo>
          <mi>m</mi>
          <msup>
            <mi>c</mi>
            <mn>2</mn>
          </msup>
        </math>
        <p>This relates energy and mass.</p>
      </div>
    </content>
  </entry>

  <!-- Test 2: MathML with fractions (quadratic formula) -->
  <entry>
    <title>The Quadratic Formula</title>
    <link href="https://example.com/mathml2"/>
    <id>https://example.com/mathml2</id>
    <updated>2006-04-15T11:00:00Z</updated>
    <content type="xhtml">
      <div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
        <p>The quadratic formula solves ax² + bx + c = 0:</p>
        <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block">
          <mi>x</mi>
          <mo>=</mo>
          <mfrac>
            <mrow>
              <mo>−</mo>
              <mi>b</mi>
              <mo>±</mo>
              <msqrt>
                <mrow>
                  <msup>
                    <mi>b</mi>
                    <mn>2</mn>
                  </msup>
                  <mo>−</mo>
                  <mn>4</mn>
                  <mi>a</mi>
                  <mi>c</mi>
                </mrow>
              </msqrt>
            </mrow>
            <mrow>
              <mn>2</mn>
              <mi>a</mi>
            </mrow>
          </mfrac>
        </math>
      </div>
    </content>
  </entry>

  <!-- Test 3: Inline MathML within text -->
  <entry>
    <title>Inline Mathematical Expressions</title>
    <link href="https://example.com/mathml3"/>
    <id>https://example.com/mathml3</id>
    <updated>2006-04-15T10:00:00Z</updated>
    <content type="xhtml">
      <div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
        <p>The area of a circle is
          <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline">
            <mi>A</mi>
            <mo>=</mo>
            <mi>π</mi>
            <msup>
              <mi>r</mi>
              <mn>2</mn>
            </msup>
          </math>
          where r is the radius.
        </p>
        <p>Similarly, the circumference is
          <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline">
            <mi>C</mi>
            <mo>=</mo>
            <mn>2</mn>
            <mi>π</mi>
            <mi>r</mi>
          </math>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </content>
  </entry>

  <!-- Test 4: MathML with summation notation -->
  <entry>
    <title>Summation Notation</title>
    <link href="https://example.com/mathml4"/>
    <id>https://example.com/mathml4</id>
    <updated>2006-04-15T09:00:00Z</updated>
    <content type="xhtml">
      <div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
        <p>The sum of the first n natural numbers:</p>
        <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block">
          <mrow>
            <munderover>
              <mo>∑</mo>
              <mrow>
                <mi>i</mi>
                <mo>=</mo>
                <mn>1</mn>
              </mrow>
              <mi>n</mi>
            </munderover>
            <mi>i</mi>
            <mo>=</mo>
            <mfrac>
              <mrow>
                <mi>n</mi>
                <mo>(</mo>
                <mi>n</mi>
                <mo>+</mo>
                <mn>1</mn>
                <mo>)</mo>
              </mrow>
              <mn>2</mn>
            </mfrac>
          </mrow>
        </math>
      </div>
    </content>
  </entry>

  <!-- Test 5: MathML security test - ensure no XSS via MathML -->
  <entry>
    <title>MathML Security Test</title>
    <link href="https://example.com/mathml5"/>
    <id>https://example.com/mathml5</id>
    <updated>2006-04-15T08:00:00Z</updated>
    <content type="xhtml">
      <div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
        <p>Attempting XSS via MathML attributes (should be sanitized):</p>
        <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" onclick="alert('XSS')" onload="alert('XSS')">
          <mi>x</mi>
          <mo>=</mo>
          <mn>42</mn>
        </math>
        <p>The math above should not execute any scripts.</p>
      </div>
    </content>
  </entry>

  <!-- Test 6: Mixed text and MathML -->
  <entry>
    <title>Pythagorean Theorem</title>
    <link href="https://example.com/mathml6"/>
    <id>https://example.com/mathml6</id>
    <updated>2006-04-15T07:00:00Z</updated>
    <content type="xhtml">
      <div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
        <p>For a right triangle with sides <em>a</em>, <em>b</em>, and hypotenuse <em>c</em>:</p>
        <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block">
          <msup>
            <mi>a</mi>
            <mn>2</mn>
          </msup>
          <mo>+</mo>
          <msup>
            <mi>b</mi>
            <mn>2</mn>
          </msup>
          <mo>=</mo>
          <msup>
            <mi>c</mi>
            <mn>2</mn>
          </msup>
        </math>
        <p>This is one of the most fundamental theorems in geometry.</p>
      </div>
    </content>
  </entry>
